      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This chassis retains its celebrated 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative feedback through the rack-and-pinion steering. The sequential turbo setup transitions smoothly, with the secondary compressor engaging reliably at 4,500 RPM. Recent preventative maintenance includes a cooling system overhaul with an upgraded aluminum radiator and a comprehensive inspection of the vacuum solenoid 'rat\u2019s nest' to ensure consistent boost pressure. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp 5-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential. While the interior and paint show signs of use consistent with an enthusiast-driven vehicle, the core mechanical components are dialed in for the street or track.",
